[2;36m                    [0m         [39mxmlParseAttribute2[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m==[0m[1;36m18[0m[39m==ABORTING[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mINFO:__main__:Running: docker run --privileged --shm-[0m[33msize[0m[39m=[0m[35m2g[0m[39m --platform linux/amd64[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m--rm -i -e [0m[33mHELPER[0m[39m=[0m[3;92mTrue[0m[39m -e [0m[33mARCHITECTURE[0m[39m=[0m[35mx86_64[0m[39m -v [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/home/user/aixcc/crete/packages/python_oss_fuzz/.oss_fuzz/build/out/[0m[95mlibxml2[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[95mout[0m[39m -v[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/tmp/[0m[95mtmpmwquezq4[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[95mtestcase[0m[39m -t ghcr.io/aixcc-finals/base-runner:v1.[0m[1;36m3.0[0m[39m reproduce xml[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m-[0m[33mruns[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m100[0m[39m.[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA fuzzing session against libxml2’s XML parser triggered an AddressSanitizer error [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mindicating a double-free in the function `xmlParseAttribute2` within `parser.c`. [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe crash occurs when processing an input XML fragment under the interactive [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfuzzing mode, leading to memory corruption and an abort.[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Issue overview  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  During a libFuzzer-driven test of the XML parser [0m[1;39m([0m[39mvia the harness in [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`fuzz/xml.c`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, AddressSanitizer reports a double-free on a small memory allocation [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[1;36m9[0m[39m bytes[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m at address `[0m[1;36m0x5020000008b0[0m[39m`. The second free occurs in [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`xmlParseAttribute2` after the same pointer was already freed earlier in the same [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfunction call sequence.[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Vulnerability type  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  This is classified as a double-free vulnerability, which can lead to undefined [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbehavior, memory corruption, and potential security risks if an attacker can [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcontrol the allocation/free pattern.[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Key observations  [0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. The pointer in question is allocated via `xmlFuzzMalloc` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mfrom `fuzz/fuzz.c`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhich delegates to `malloc` through the fuzzing allocator, then immediately used by[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`xmlStrndup` [0m[1;39m([0m[39min `xmlstring.c`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. `xmlParseAttribute2` in `parser.c` contains two distinct code paths that both [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcall `[0m[1;35mfree[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` on the same pointer without clearing or resetting it, leading to the [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdouble-free during attribute parsing.  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. The error stack traces show the initial free at line [0m[1;36m9024[0m[39m of `parser.c` and [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe second free at line [0m[1;36m9028[0m[39m of the same function, both executed in the context of [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mparsing a start tag [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`xmlParseStartTag2`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and then unwinding through the element [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mparsing routines.  [0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m. The fuzz harness entrypoint [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput` in `fuzz/xml.[0m[1;92mc:68[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msimply invokes `xmlCtxtParseDocument`, demonstrating that the issue resides [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mentirely within the parser logic and not in the harness itself.[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Code areas for further investigation  [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • `parser.c:xmlParseAttribute2` – examine allocation and deallocation logic for [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mattribute values, particularly around lines [0m[1;36m9009[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m9028[0m[39m.  [0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • `parser.c:xmlParseStartTag2`, `xmlParseElementStart`, `xmlParseElement`, and [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`xmlParseDocument` – review how attribute parsing integrates with higher‐level [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39melement parsing and error handling.  [0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • `fuzz/fuzz.c:xmlFuzzMalloc` and `xmlstring.c:xmlStrndup` – verify fuzzing [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mallocator behavior and string duplication routines to ensure correct ownership and [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlifetime semantics.  [0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Fuzzer harness [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`fuzz/xml.c`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m – while not the root cause, confirm that no [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munusual flags or command‐line options alter memory management semantics in the [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mparser.[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe fuzzer run on libxml2 produced an AddressSanitizer double-free in the parser’s [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mxmlParseAttribute2 function. The stack trace showed two frees of the same [0m[1;36m9[0m[39m-byte [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbuffer [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`internal_val`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, once at line [0m[1;36m9024[0m[39m and again at line [0m[1;36m9028[0m[39m of parser.c. The [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mattempted patch removed the second conditional `[0m[1;35mxmlFree[0m[1;39m([0m[39minternal_val[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`. After [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mapplying the patch, the repository reconfigured and rebuilt without compile errors,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconfirming the duplicate‐free code was removed.[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Initial Issue  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - A libFuzzer invocation of `LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput` on an XML input triggered [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAddressSanitizer’s “attempting double-free” error.  [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The buffer at address `[0m[1;36m0x5020000008b0[0m[39m` was malloc’d in xmlParseAttribute2 [0m[1;39m([0m[39mvia[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mxmlFuzzMalloc → xmlStrndup[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and freed twice in the same function.  [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Key stack frames:  [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     * Allocation: xmlFuzzMalloc → xmlStrndup → xmlParseAttribute2 [0m[1;39m([0m[39mparser.[0m[1;92mc:9009[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     * First free: xmlParseAttribute2 [0m[1;39m([0m[39mparser.[0m[1;92mc:9024[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     * Second free: xmlParseAttribute2 [0m[1;39m([0m[39mparser.[0m[1;92mc:9028[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The repeated free caused the sanitizer abort, indicating a serious [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmemory‐management bug in attribute parsing.[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Patch Attempt  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In parser.c, the block around line [0m[1;36m9024[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m9028[0m[39m was edited: the conditional `if [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39minternal_val[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;35mxmlFree[0m[1;39m([0m[39minternal_val[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;` was removed and replaced with a comment [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnoting the single free above was sufficient.  [0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The patch diff:  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```diff[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     --- a/parser.c[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     +++ b/parser.c[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     @@ [0m[1;36m-9024[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m9[0m[39m +[0m[1;36m9024[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m7[0m[39m @@[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;35mxmlFree[0m[1;39m([0m[39minternal_val[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     -   if [0m[1;39m([0m[39minternal_val[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     -       [0m[1;35mxmlFree[0m[1;39m([0m[39minternal_val[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     -   [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     +   [0m[35m/[0m[39m* internal_val was freed above; no further free needed *[0m[35m/[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This change eliminates the second free call.[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Patch Result  [0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - After applying the patch, the build script reran autoconf/libtool and [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconfigure without errors.  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - A full `make all-recursive` completed successfully, compiling all C files [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mincluding parser.c.  [0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No further sanitizer run was shown, but the compilation logs confirm the patch[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mapplied cleanly and did not break the build.[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Areas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The xmlParseAttribute2 implementation in parser.c around lines [0m[1;36m8980[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m9060[0m[39m: [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mverify all code paths free exactly once.  [0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The xmlParseStartTag2 calls into xmlParseAttribute2: ensure no overlapping [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfrees when processing nested or repeated attributes.  [0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The interaction between xmlFuzzMalloc [0m[1;39m([0m[39mfuzz.c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and xmlFree: confirm custom [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmalloc doesn’t introduce its own double‐free scenarios.  [0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Similar patterns in other parsing functions [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., xmlParseAttributeValue, [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mxmlParseElementStart[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to catch any analogous memory errors.[0m                         [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe initial issue is an AddressSanitizer-detected double‐free in libxml2’s XML [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mparser. During fuzzing, `xmlParseAttribute2` frees the same buffer [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`internal_val`[0m[1;39m)[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtwice, leading to an abort. The patch attempt removes the second, unconditional [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mxmlFree[0m[1;39m([0m[39minternal_val[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` in `parser.c` [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround line [0m[1;36m9024[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, under the comment that [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`internal_val` was already freed. After applying the patch, the library [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreconfigures and recompiles cleanly under AddressSanitizer and the fuzzing build [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mflags, with no build errors reported.[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Initial Issue  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - A double‐free is reported by AddressSanitizer when running the libFuzzer [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mharness against libxml2.  [0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The error stack traces back to `xmlParseAttribute2` in `parser.c`, where [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`internal_val` is freed twice in different execution branches.  [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Key log excerpts:  [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • First free:  [0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       `#[0m[1;36m1[0m[39m xmlParseAttribute2 … parser.[0m[1;92mc:9024:17[0m[39m`  [0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Second free:  [0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       `#[0m[1;36m1[0m[39m xmlParseAttribute2 … parser.[0m[1;92mc:9028:13[0m[39m`  [0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Both frees act on the same [0m[1;36m9[0m[39m-byte allocation made via `xmlFuzzMalloc` → [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`xmlStrndup`.[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Patch Attempt  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In `parser.c` around line [0m[1;36m9024[0m[39m, the code originally had:  [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```c[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     if [0m[1;39m([0m[39minternal_val[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;35mxmlFree[0m[1;39m([0m[39minternal_val[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```  [0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     immediately following an earlier free of `internal_val` in another branch.  [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The patch removes these four lines [0m[1;39m([0m[39mthe `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39minternal_val[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` test and its body[0m[1;39m)[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand adds a comment:  [0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```diff[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     -        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39minternal_val[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     -            [0m[1;35mxmlFree[0m[1;39m([0m[39minternal_val[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     -        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     +        [0m[35m/[0m[39m* internal_val was freed above; no further free needed *[0m[35m/[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```  [0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The context is inside the closing brace of an `if` that already handles [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfreeing `internal_val`.[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Patch Result  [0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - After applying the diff, the build system re-ran `autogen`, `configure`, and [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`make` under Clang with `-[0m[33mfsanitize[0m[39m=[0m[35maddress[0m[39m`.  [0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The logs show successful detection of compiler flags, configuration steps, and[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcompilation of all libxml2 components [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., `buf.c`, `entities.c`, etc.[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m without [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39merrors.  [0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No further sanitizer failures or build errors are shown in the truncated log.[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Areas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The logic in `xmlParseAttribute2` and its callers [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`xmlParseStartTag2`, [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`xmlParseElementStart`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m should be reviewed to ensure that all allocation/free paths[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mare balanced.  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The interaction between `xmlFuzzMalloc`, `xmlStrndup`, and `xmlFree` across [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdifferent parsing branches should be audited for consistent ownership.  [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Any other code paths in attribute parsing that manipulate `internal_val` or [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msimilar temporaries may hide additional double-free or use-after-free issues.[0m       [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mparser.[0m[1;92mc:9028[0m[39m.  [0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The allocation originates from `xmlFuzzMalloc` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mfuzz.c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m followed by an in‐place [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mduplication via `xmlStrndup` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mxmlstring.c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The duplicate frees occur along the parsing call chain:  [0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  xmlParseAttribute2 → xmlParseStartTag2 → xmlParseElementStart → xmlParseElement →[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mxmlParseDocument → xmlCtxtParseDocument → LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput.[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mImportant Observations  [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The double-free happens unconditionally when `internal_val` is non‐NULL, [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mindicating missing or duplicated control logic around its deallocation.  [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The sanitizer log includes detailed backtraces for allocation and both [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdeallocations, confirming it is the same heap region being freed twice.  [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The harness entry point [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m merely drives inputs into the [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mparser and is not the root cause.[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch Attempt  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- In `parser.c` around line [0m[1;36m9024[0m[39m, the conditional block that frees `internal_val` [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mif non‐NULL was expanded to include two consecutive frees: one inside an `if [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39minternal_val[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m [0m[1;35mxmlFree[0m[1;39m([0m[39minternal_val[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m; [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m` block and another identical free [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mimmediately afterward.  [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The patch removes the second `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39minternal_val[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;35mxmlFree[0m[1;39m([0m[39minternal_val[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;` clause [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand replaces it with a comment:  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[35m/[0m[39m* internal_val was freed above; no further free needed *[0m[35m/[0m[39m  [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- This change collapses the two frees into a single deallocation to address the [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdouble-free.[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch Application and Build Log  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- After applying the patch, the standard configure/autotools sequence ran without [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39merrors.  [0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The project was rebuilt under AddressSanitizer and fuzzing instrumentation flags [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`-[0m[33mfsanitize[0m[39m=[0m[35maddress[0m[39m`, `-[0m[33mfsanitize[0m[39m=[0m[35mfuzzer[0m[39m-no-link`, etc.[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Compilation of all major modules [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`buf.c`, `chvalid.c`, `dict.c`, etc.[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m completed[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msuccessfully, with no sanitizer or compile-time errors reported up to the truncated[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbuild log.[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAreas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The control flow in `xmlParseAttribute2` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mparser.c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m around `internal_val` [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mallocation, usage, and deallocation to ensure no other code paths lead to double or[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmissing frees.  [0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Interaction between `xmlParseAttribute2` and higher-level start-tag parsing [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mroutines [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`xmlParseStartTag2`, `xmlParseElementStart`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m for consistent ownership and[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlifetime of attribute value buffers.  [0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Memory allocation wrappers used for fuzzing [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`xmlFuzzMalloc` in fuzz.c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mduplication routines [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`xmlStrndup` in xmlstring.c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to confirm they integrate [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcorrectly with the parser’s free logic.  [0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Any conditional branches in attribute parsing that may skip or repeat [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdeallocation, potentially leading to similar or new memory-management issues.[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
